<HEAD>
<TITLE>CEI: Fred L. Smith</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="009900" VLINK="000099">

<IMG SRC="fred.gif" ALT="Photo of Fred Smith" ALIGN="right" HSPACE="15" VSPACE="5" BORDER="0">

<P>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H1>Fred L. Smith</H1>
</CENTER>

<P>
<BR>

Fred Smith is President and Founder of the <A HREF="/cei.html">Competitive Enterprise
Institute</A>.  Mr. Smith speaks and writes on a wide range of economic and
environmental topics.  Frequently, Mr. Smith is a guest on various radio and
television programs where he debates free-market approaches to vexing public
policy problems.  He has appeared on national news programs including
<i>MacNeil/Lehrer</I> and <i>Crossfire</I>.  He co-edited the book
<I>Environmental Politics:  Public Costs, Private Rewards</i> (Praeger, 1992), and his work appears frequently in newspapers and magazines.   Before founding
CEI, Mr. Smith served as the Director of Government Relations for the Council
for a Competitive Economy, and as a senior research economist for the
Association of American Railroads, and for five years as a senior policy
analyst at the Environmental Protection Agency.<P>

