<HEAD>
<TITLE>CEI: Quote of the Week, August 26, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="009900" VLINK="000099">


<IMG SRC="/images/quote.gif" ALT="Quote of the Week" HEIGHT=115 WIDTH=149 ALIGN=left VSPACE=5 HSPACE=15>
<P>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
"The American people realize, even if far too many do not within the
Washington establishment, that a government that tries to do everything,
will do nothing very well. Good government, by definition, is less government."

<P ALIGN=RIGHT>--<a href="fred.html">Fred L. Smith</A>

<P><A HREF="/publist1.html#update">CEI UpDate</A>, <I>January 1995)</I>
<P>
<BR>
<CENTER>
See also: <A HREF="/quotes.html">Quote of the Week Archive</A>
