<HEAD>
<TITLE>CEI: Sellout of the Month, August</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="000000" LINK="009900" VLINK="000099">



<IMG SRC="/images/sellout.gif" ALT="Sellout Logo" WDITH=115 HEIGHT=110 ALIGN=left VSPACE=5 HSPACE=15>
<BR>
<BR>

<P>When the International Whaling Commission (IWC) convened in Aberdeen,
Scotland last month, the United States delegation strongly supported a
request by the Makah Indians to take five Gray whales. The Makah, a small
tribe from Washington state, were following a precedent well established by
the IWC, but midway through the meeting, the House Resources Committee
passed a unanimous resolution opposing the Makah request. That contributed
to an about face by the US delegation, which pulled its support during the
meeting. Denying the Makah request is shameful. Unlike Congress, the Makah
long ago recognized the important link between ownership and stewardship and have sensibly conserved their resources for centuries.

<P>
<BR>
<CENTER>
