</BODY>
</HTML>␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀tom4.html␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀100644 ␀  1647 ␀   144 ␀       5514  6061647140  11025␀ 0␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀ustar  ␀cei␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀users␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>CEI: Tom Miller</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF">

<A NAME="top"></A>

<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H1>Tom Miller </H1>
</CENTER>

<BR>
<BR>

<P>Tom Miller is the Senior Policy Analyst at the Competitive Enterprise
Institute, a non-partisan public interest group committed to advancing the
principles of free enterprise and limited government.  Based in Washington,
D.C., the Institute is founded on the belief that free markets and individual
liberty  best serve the public interest, while politicians and bureaucrats best
serve themselves.  <p>
<p>
Mr. Miller directs the <A HREF="errp.html">Economic Policy and Regulatory Reform program</A> at CEI.
As CEI&#146;s Senior Policy Analyst since 1986, his primary focus has been on
issues of financial services regulation, health care insurance, entitlement
programs reform, and antitrust regulation.  Mr. Miller is the author of <I>A
Citizen&#146;s Guide To Banking Reform</I>, described by Representative Dick
Armey as &#147;A lucid, rigorous, and refreshingly accessible treatment of a
complicated and important subject.&#148; He is editor of the annual Competitive
Enterprise Index, which analyzes all congressional votes judged to have a
significant impact on competition, freedom, and opportunity in the U.S.
economy. <p>
<p>
Prior to joining CEI, Mr. Miller was a trial attorney, a broadcaster, and a
journalist.  At the firm of Powell, Goldstein, Frazer &amp; Murphy in Atlanta,
his litigation activities included personal injury, insurance defense, criminal
defense, medical malpractice, and copyright cases.  Mr. Miller was a news
director at radio stations in Rome, Georgia and Anderson, South Carolina; a
sportscaster and talk show host at radio stations in Charlotte, North Carolina
and Atlanta; a writer/producer for current affairs programs at the Voice of
America; and a consulting producer for two television programs, &#147;The
McLaughlin Group&#148; and &#147;John McLaughlin One-on-One.&#148;  Mr. Miller
was also a free lance writer on continuing assignment for <I>Reader&#146;s
Digest</I> and an investigative reporter for syndicated columnist Donald
Lambro.  <p>
<p>
Mr. Miller received his law degree from Duke Law School and a B.A. cum laude in
political science from New York University.  He is a member of the State Bar of
Georgia.   <p>
<p>
Mr. Miller&#146;s work on public policy issues has appeared in such
publications as <I>The Wall Street Journal, Reader&#146;s Digest, Reason,
American Spectator, Insight, Consumers Research, Los Angeles Times, Washington
Times, and Cleveland Plain Dealer</I>.<p>
<p>
CEI is supported solely by donations from foundations, corporations, and
individuals; it accepts no government funds and does not perform contractual
work.<p>


<BR>
