<H1>THE TRUE STATE OF THE PLANET</H1>
edited by Ronald Bailey
</CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>

<IMG SRC="en6295.gif" ALT="Photo of *True State* book" ALIGN="right" HSPACE="15" VSPACE="5">

<P>Chapter Summaries:

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="tru1.html">Chapter 1: Population, Food, and Income</A> 
<LI><A HREF="tru2.html">Chapter 2: Saving the Planet with Pesticides: Increasing Food Supplies</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru3.html">Chapter 3: Global Warming: Messy Models, Decent Data, and Pointless Policy</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru4.html">Chapter 4: The Coming Age of Abundance</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru5.html">Chapter 5: The Causes and Prevention of Cancer</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru6.html">Chapter 6: Forests: Conflicting Signals</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru7.html">Chapter 7: Conserving Biodiversity Resources for the Future</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru8.html">Chapter 8: Water Options for the Blue Planet</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru9.html">Chapter 9: Rescuing the Oceans</A>
<LI><A HREF="tru10.html">Chapter 10: Richer is Cleaner--Long Term Trends in Global Air Quality</A>

